# Push workflow

The user works in `cutline-studio` and should never need to run git commands manually.

## Deploy code (primary trigger)

When the user message is exactly **`CLN-FULL-DEPLOY`** or contains that token (case-sensitive), run the full deploy workflow below. No other interpretation.

Meaning of **`CLN-FULL-DEPLOY`**: commit all changes in `cutline-studio`, then `npm run push` — personal demo `main`, live site `gh-pages` build, company `cutline-2.0` → `web/`. Never substitute raw `git push` only.

Also honor: **"full deploy"**, **"ship it"**, **"deploy everything"**, "push my changes", "upload to github", or "ship it — commit and push everything":

1. Commit any uncommitted changes in `cutline-studio` (use a clear message from the diff).
2. Run `npm run push` from the `cutline-studio` directory (never substitute raw `git push` only).
3. Report what landed:
   - Personal demo source: `Awdyx/cutline-studio-demo` → `main`
   - Fresh iPad demo: `Awdyx/cutline-studio-play` → `main` (when remote configured)
   - Live demo: same repo → `gh-pages` (built Pages artifact)
   - Company: `Cutline-Tutoring/cutline-2.0` → `web/` on branch `master` (rsync + commit if needed)

Do not ask them to open terminals, switch repos, or run scripts themselves.
